"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756488","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government Property Unit (GPU) has only commissioned three Strategic Annual Management Plans (SAMPs) from Government departments, on an annual basis, since 2014.</p><p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office submitted a SAMP to the GPU in 2015 and in 2016. The SAMP for 2017 is being completed.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:09:11.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756488/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756488/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756489","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold information on applications for a) internal loans and b) secondments from civil servants received in 2010 and 2011. The information on applications received between 2012 and 2017 is not held centrally and cannot be provided without exceeding the disproportionate cost threshold.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-11T15:39:00.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756489/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756489/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756490","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>An estimate of the number of arms-length bodies that will be established on our exit from the EU will be undertaken as the negotiations with the EU proceed.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-12T15:42:21.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756490/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756490/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756491","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>​It does.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-12T15:34:16.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756491/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756491/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756491/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756492","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>All requests for consultancy and temporary staff must be accompanied by a formal business case. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office's process for external recruitment is in compliance with Cabinet Office recruitment controls.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-11T15:44:59.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756492/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756492/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756492/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756493","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) defines 'consultancy' and 'temporary' staff as agency staff; contingent staff; and contractors.</p><p>In the Financial Year 2016/17, in compliance with Cabinet Office recruitment controls, the FCO's Chief Operating Officer approved 23 out of 25 requests for the recruitment of temporary staff for London-based roles. All approvals were for the recruitment of temporary staff paid on a daily rate.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","7974","2017-09-11T15:43:35.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756493/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756493/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756493/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756494","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) defines 'consultancy' and 'temporary' staff as agency staff; contingent staff; and contractors.</p><p>In the Financial Year 2016/17, in compliance with Cabinet Office recruitment controls, the FCO's Chief Operating Officer approved 23 out of 25 requests for the recruitment of temporary staff for London-based roles. All approvals were for the recruitment of temporary staff paid on a daily rate.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","7932","2017-09-11T15:43:35.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756494/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756494/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756494/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756495","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-12","<p>Defra places appropriate contractual obligations on our supply chain to ensure that they have the correct security vetting and relevant training in place.</p><p> </p><p>All suppliers are obliged to provide extensive cyber awareness training to their staff and their suppliers and contractors.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-12T15:38:59.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756495/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756495/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756495/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756496","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-13","<p>We provided a Strategic Asset Management Plan to the Government Property Unit in 2014/15, 2015/16 and 2017/18.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-13T16:40:26.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756496/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756496/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756496/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756497","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-18","<p>This department is committed to the benefits that can be brought for the taxpayer in the delivery of Government objectives from interchange and is always looking for opportunities to develop arrangements that further the delivery agenda of the Department.</p><p>It is the policy across Civil Service departments that where individuals transfer temporarily between our department and another department they move on a loan basis.</p><p>We do not centrally monitor, in the department, if a Civil Servant applies for a loan or secondment out of the department, each request is dealt with on a case-by-case basis in line with business need.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-18T15:05:59.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756497/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756497/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756497/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756498","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-12","<p>All requests for consultancy and temporary staff over £25,000 are approved by the Defra Gateway Approval Panel.</p><p> </p><p>However, the proportion of engagements over and under this threshold is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-12T15:17:55.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756498/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756498/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756498/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756499","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-12","<p>All requests for consultancy and temporary staff must be accompanied by a formal business case.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-12T15:20:17.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756499/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756499/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756499/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756500","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-12T16:52:35.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756500/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756500/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756500/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756501","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-13","<p>The UK’s relationship with the EU's agencies upon exit will be evaluated in light of delivering the twelve objectives outlined by the Prime Minister to achieve a deep and special partnership between the UK and the EU. The UK’s future relationship with the EU's decentralised bodies after leaving the EU is a matter for the negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>Prior to any decisions on establishing new agencies, the Government will, however, always look to minimise disruption and costs, which will include considering alternative options.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-09-13T16:54:49.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756501/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756501/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756501/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756502","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Defra group, which includes the Environment Agency, has been delivering an integrated ‘group-wide’ property rationalisation plan since 2010. As a result annual property running costs, which include depots, were reduced by over £60 million by 2015, with a further £37 million in savings expected by 2020.</p><p>Depots represent a relatively small proportion of property costs, which since 2015 have been reduced from £6.2 million to £5.8 million per year.</p><p>The Environment Agency undertakes periodic reviews of its depot requirement, and how this is met. Depots are used for storing equipment and are a key part of the Environment Agency’s flood and pollution incident management capability and response infrastructure. Rationalisation is considered in that context.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-09-12T12:42:49.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756502/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756502/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756502/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Environment Agency: Operating Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate he has made of the potential savings to the public purse of the reduction in Environment Agency depot costs.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756503","Department for Education","false","2017-09-12","<p>It is departmental policy that all contracts, where cyber security is relevant, impose an obligation on contractors to obtain Cyber Essentials certification and demonstrate conformance to, and show evidence of conformance to the ISO/IEC 27001 (Information Security Management Systems Requirements) standard, including the application of controls from ISO/IEC 27002 (Code of Practice for Information Security Controls). Additionally all contractor or sub-contractor employees who handle Departmental Data must have annual awareness training in protecting information.</p><p> </p><p>All contractors with access to the DfE network are prompted at login to read the DfE Acceptable Use Policies. These policies set out the conditions for the official and personal use of the Department’s Information Technology and Security policy framework.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-09-12T16:23:39.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756503/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756503/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756503/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-04","Department for Education: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756504","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The financial figures quoted in each of the questions are the total staff costs as published in the Ministry of Defence (MOD) Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17 in £000's, and include salaries and wages, social security, pensions, and severance, as well as redundancy payments.</p><p>Of the £12,533 paid in redundancy and severance payments to both Armed Forces and civilian personnel set out in the MOD Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17; £402 was paid to male Armed Forces personnel. No payments were made to female Armed Forces personnel.</p><p>Of the £44,133 paid in redundancy and severance payments to both Armed Forces and civilian personnel set out in the MOD Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, for the year 2015-16; £9,713 was paid to male Armed Forces personnel and £1,395 was paid to female Armed Forces personnel.</p><p>In line with department policy, values have been rounded to the nearest £000.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","8368","2017-09-12T16:17:48.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756504/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756504/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756504/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 6 July 2017 to Question 3361, on redundancy, how much of the £9,776,731 paid in redundancy payments to armed forces staff in 2016-17 was paid to (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756505","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department has not submitted a Strategic Asset Management Plan in any of the last ten years.</p><p>The Government Property Unit (GPU) re-commissioned Strategic Asset Management Plans in 2014. From 2014 to 2016 the Ministry of Defence (MOD) was working on the Better Defence Estate Strategy announced in November 2016. It was agreed with the GPU that the MOD was not in a position to compile a Strategic Asset Management Plan until this work had been completed.</p><p>A Strategic Asset Management Plan will be submitted in 2017.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-12T16:36:14.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756505/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756505/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756505/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756506","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-12T13:45:02.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756506/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756506/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756506/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756507","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) delegates authority to approve the use of consultants and temporary staff to each Top Level Budget (TLB) holder. Information on the process employed in each TLB is not held centrally. However, where the MOD does contract for private-sector support, it must be fully justifiable and provide value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7949","2017-09-12T13:50:45.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756507/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756507/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756507/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756508","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) delegates authority to approve the use of consultants and temporary staff to each Top Level Budget (TLB) holder. Information on the process employed in each TLB is not held centrally. However, where the MOD does contract for private-sector support, it must be fully justifiable and provide value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7970","2017-09-12T13:50:45.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756508/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756508/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756508/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7949"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756509","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>All consultancy contracts awarded through the Crown Commercial Services framework which are currently live are priced on a time and materials basis, and the time component will be against agreed rates. The contract payments will typically be against completion of contract milestones.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-12T13:46:56.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756509/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756509/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756509/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7928"
