"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756538","Department of Health","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department has procedures in place to comply with Cabinet Office Efficiency controls ensuring that all requests for consultancy or temporary staff are subject to approval by formal panels. These panels provide the ultimate approval based upon business case submissions.</p><p> </p><p>We do not recognise the term ‘resource board’, however, the process for approving professional services spend is via a professional services business case (PSBC) that gets approved by the Finance Approvals Panel (FAP). Temporary staff are approved via one of two routes:</p><p> </p><p>- Specialist Contractors = PSBC to secretariat then FAP</p><p> </p><p>- Admin and Clerical = complete a ‘Request to Recruit’ Form (which is a proportionate type of business case) which is then submitted via a secretariat.</p><p> </p><p>With regard to the question on rates, the Department does hold this information on its electronic procurement system from which the proportion of consultants on daily rates could be calculated, however, this would require a review of each individual contract to check the payment method, and would result in disproportionate cost. We are not therefore able to provide this information.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","7933 ; 7975","2017-09-12T14:47:35.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756538/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756538/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756538/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-04","Department of Health: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756539","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>At this stage, the MoJ has not identified the need to create any new arms-length bodies as a result of the UK’s exit from the EU.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-09-11T16:58:07.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756539/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756539/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756539/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756540","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>None of the requests for Consultancy or Temporary staff are approved via a resource board. However, each request has a formal business case which must be approved via HR, Finance, and a Director General, before it can be progressed.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T15:23:27.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756540/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756540/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756540/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756541","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government Property Unit has commissioned Strategic Asset Management Plans (SAMPs) from departments on an annual basis since 2014. The SAMP articulates the property aspects of a department's business and forms part of the overall planning framework in government linked to each Single Departmental Plan. In some cases, where there are significant changes to a department's remit (such as following a machinery of government change or major business reviews), the timing of a SAMP refresh may be aligned with the broader strategy for the department. Information is provided regularly to the Government Property Unit about the management of the department’s property assets and Executive Summaries of SAMPs will be published for the first time in Autumn 2017.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T16:57:39.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756541/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756541/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756541/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756542","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>We can confirm that all requirements within the last 12 month period for Consultancy and Temporary Staff followed a process for procurement which includes a formal business case to be completed.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T15:25:37.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756542/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756542/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756542/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756543","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T15:27:26.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756543/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756543/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756543/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756544","Leader of the House","false","2017-09-08","<p>The new Petitions Committee will consider petitions which reached the 100,000 threshold for debate as soon as it is set up.</p><p> </p><p>As the petitions system is part of the official work of Parliament, it stops when Parliament dissolves. This applies not just to petitions but also to other kinds of business, such as parliamentary questions and early day motions.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2017-09-08T16:28:50.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756544/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756544/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756544/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2017-09-04","e-petitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, for what reasons petitions on the e-petitions website were not carried over from the beginning of purdah on 3 May 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756545","Leader of the House","false","2017-09-08","<p>In the period of 3 May 2017 to 4 September 2017 the e-petitions website was visited 1,000,647 times.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2017-09-08T16:28:59.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756545/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756545/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756545/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2017-09-04","e-petitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how many times the e-petitions website was visited between 3 May 2017 to 4 September 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756546","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested is not held by my Department and to create it would incur a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-09-12T15:39:29.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756546/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756546/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756546/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-09-04","Northern Ireland Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756547","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Northern Ireland Office submits its strategic asset management plan as part of the Cabinet Office’s affiliated cluster.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-09-12T15:41:21.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756547/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756547/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756547/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-09-04","Northern Ireland Office: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756548","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department’s resourcing policy requires all requests for resources, including consultancy and temporary staff, to be approved by the departmental Resources Review Panel.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-09-11T11:38:24.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756548/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756548/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756548/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-09-04","Northern Ireland Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756549","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>My Department employs professionally qualified officials and utilises expertise from other Government bodies to reduce its requirement for consultancy assignments. However in the 2016-17 financial year, the Department has procured three consultancy assignments, two of which have been paid at a daily rate.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-09-12T16:41:20.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756549/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756549/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756549/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-09-04","Northern Ireland Office: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756550","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department’s resourcing policy requires all requests for resources, including consultancy and temporary staff, to be submitted as a formal business case to the departmental Resources Review Panel.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2017-09-11T11:39:44.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756550/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756550/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756550/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-09-04","Northern Ireland Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756551","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>Compensations payments are based on a calculation using the exit scheme tariff, length of service, pensionable salary, and pension scheme. Between 1 November 2016 and 31 March 2017, 56 employers left the department under a Voluntary Exit scheme, and the male female split of payments is shown in the following table;</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Exits</p></td><td><p>Departures</p></td><td><p>Cost (£)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>56</p></td><td><p>2,415,060.16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>£1,306,033.12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>£1,109,027.04</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T15:23:26.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756551/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756551/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756551/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 13 July 2017 to Question 3367, how much of the £2,415,060 paid in exit packages to Ministry of Justice staff was paid to (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756552","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>Contracts with CRCs require each CRC to ensure that it employs a sufficient level of suitably trained staff. As I said in my response to PQ 7699, we manage providers robustly to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitments and take action where any provider falls short of its obligations.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","7701","2017-09-12T11:01:47.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756552/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756552/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756552/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 12 July 2017 to Question 2785, what mechanisms are in place to ensure that community rehabilitation company staff are adequately trained.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756553","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>Contracts with CRCs require each CRC to ensure that it employs a sufficient level of suitably trained staff. As I said in my response to PQ 7699, we manage providers robustly to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitments and take action where any provider falls short of its obligations.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","7700","2017-09-12T11:01:47.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756553/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756553/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756553/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 12 July 2017 to Question 2785, what mechanisms are in place to ensure that community rehabilitation company staff are paid a living wage.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756554","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>A total of £37.15m was paid to CRCs above their agreed contracts in 2016/17. These payments were made for a variety of reasons and cannot be broken down by CRC because the information is commercially sensitive. Furthermore, some concessions were agreed with CRCs on a case-by-case basis to enable them to re-invest contractual payment deductions in key areas of the business and improve services.</p><p>In addition, we have made changes to how CRCs are paid for future years so they can focus on activities that best rehabilitate offenders and keep society safe. This additional investment will see projected payments to providers being no higher than originally budgeted for at the time of the reforms. A summary of the variations can be found below. Relevant OJEU notices can be found at http://ted.europa.eu/udl?uri=TED:NOTICE:45770-2015:TEXT:EN:HTML&amp;tabId=4</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-09-12T11:10:38.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756554/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756554/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756554/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much by each contract each community rehabilitation company in England and Wales received in additional funding above their agreed contracts in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756555","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>The MoJ ensures that cyber security awareness of its staff and suppliers is at a level proportionate to the technical services they provide and their interaction with MoJ system. This is done through:</p><ul><li><p>Adherence to cyber security standards enforced through contracts,</p></li><li><p>Required vetting at different levels for those with access to sensitive data or transactions,</p></li><li><p>And generally raising awareness through various MoJ and National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) communications.</p></li></ul>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T15:25:28.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756555/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756555/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756555/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756556","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>We can confirm that within the last 12 month period, all consultancy assignments that have been procured via the Contract and Commercial Management Directorate were paid a daily rate calculated against a number of days to complete the programme.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-12T15:28:01.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756556/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756556/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756556/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Ministry of Justice: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756557","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>As we leave the EU, we will consider appropriate mechanisms for delivering our priorities. My Department has no current plans to establish new arms-length bodies as a result of leaving the EU.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-11T17:00:33.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756557/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756557/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756557/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the number of new arms-length bodies her Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756558","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>The number of applications DFID has received for internal loans from existing civil servants applying through Civil Service Jobs (from November 2012) is:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Number of Applicants</p></td><td><p>Loans</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>36</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>85</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>45</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>75</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>285</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Information prior to November 2012 is not available.</p><p> </p><p>Existing Civil Servants apply to DFID on loan, and not secondment.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-09-11T16:02:04.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756558/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756558/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756558/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many applications her Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756559","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>DFID has submitted annual Strategic Asset Management Plans since these were first commissioned by the Government Property Unit (GPU) in 2014.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-09-11T16:02:52.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756559/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756559/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756559/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, in which of the last 10 years her Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756560","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>Within DFID’s approved workforce plans, temporary staff may be appointed on fixed term contracts if there is a need. Any additional resourcing needs, including consultancy and temporary staff, must be approved on the basis of a business case.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","7956","2017-09-12T14:45:17.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756560/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756560/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756560/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for her Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756561","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>The information is not held in the form requested and can only be collated at disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-09-11T16:01:15.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756561/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756561/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756561/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by her Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756562","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>Within DFID’s approved workforce plans, temporary staff may be appointed on fixed term contracts if there is a need. Any additional resourcing needs, including consultancy and temporary staff, must be approved on the basis of a business case.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","7977","2017-09-12T14:45:17.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756562/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756562/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756562/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the her Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756563","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>All requests for consultancy, and contingent labour are required to be supported by a business case.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-12T12:25:26.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756563/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756563/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756563/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the her Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756564","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Home Department tries its upmost to avoid awarding contracts based solely around a day rate time and materials approach. The majority (over 98% in the case of this Financial Year) are contracted on maximum, capped or fixed cost basis.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-12T13:35:57.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756564/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756564/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756564/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by her Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756565","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>With the exception of Agency Workers allocated to Frontline Roles (where the roles are public or industry facing) all requests for consultancy and temporary staff are approved by the Resource Board.</p><p>For Frontline Agency roles the responsibility for approval is delegated to the Command Director General.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-12T13:37:49.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756565/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756565/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756565/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for her Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756566","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government Property Unit has commissioned Strategic Asset Management Plans (SAMPs) from departments on an annual basis since 2014.</p><p>The SAMP articulates the property aspects of a department's business and forms part of the overall planning framework in government linked to each Single Departmental Plan. In some cases, where there are significant changes to a Department's remit (such as following a machinery of government change or major business reviews), the timing of a SAMP refresh may be aligned with the broader strategy for the Department.</p><p>Information is provided regularly to the Government Property Unit about the management of the department’s property assets and Executive Summaries of SAMPs will be published for the first time in Autumn 2017.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-12T11:31:44.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756566/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756566/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756566/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, in which of the last 10 years her Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756567","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Home Office only holds central records for job applications since April 2014; since that time 4830 applications were received for roles advertised as loans and secondments through Civil Service Jobs.</p><p>The data on whether these applications came from existing civil servants or other eligible NDPB people is not held.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-12T12:03:55.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756567/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756567/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756567/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications her Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756568","Home Office","false","2017-10-09","<p>The policy set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the National Cyber Security Strategy applies to everyone employed by the Home Office, including contractors.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office is committed to ensuring that contractors and their staff have a sound awareness of cyber risk matters and they take all necessary safeguards to protect the department’s information.</p><p> </p><p>Cyber security awareness, the need to ensure contractual compliance with Information Assurance standards such as ISO 27001:2013 certification and “Cyber Essentials/ Plus” is included in contract specifications and reviewed as part of the evaluation process. Contractors must comply with the department’s IT security policies and procedures.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-10-09T16:06:06.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756568/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756568/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756568/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756569","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>The principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by DFID where appropriate. This is in line with our standard terms and conditions which state:</p><p>‘Where required in accordance with Section 3 (Terms of Reference) and tender documentation, the Supplier shall obtain and maintain certification under the HM Government Cyber Essentials Scheme at the level set out in Section 3 (Terms of Reference) and tender documentation.’</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-09-11T16:03:32.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756569/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756569/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756569/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Department for International Development: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756570","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>Whether or not any new arms-length bodies will be required by the Home Office once the UK has left the EU, remains subject to a final assessment and is in part dependent on the outcome of negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>Prior to any decisions on establishing new bodies, the Government will, however, always look to minimise disruption and costs, which will include considering alternative options.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T13:13:11.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756570/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756570/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756570/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Home Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of new arms-length bodies her Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756571","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Payments to men account for 77 per cent and payments to women account for 23 per cent.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T16:44:41.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756571/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756571/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756571/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 6 July 2017 to Question 3368 on redundancy, how much of the £17,011,102 paid out in exit packages in 2016-17 was given to (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756572","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Payments to men accounted for 82 per cent and payments to women accounted for 18 per cent.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T13:14:27.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756572/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756572/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756572/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 6 July 2017 to Question 3368 on redundancy, how much of the £17,987,001 paid out in exit payments in 2015-16 was given to (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756573","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department’s current assessment is that any additional transport-related functions falling to the Government after EU exit can be undertaken by existing bodies.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-12T10:07:38.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756573/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756573/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756573/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756574","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-11T09:53:13.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756574/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756574/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756574/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756575","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The HR Departmental Approvals Committee (DAC) approves Contingent Labour spend and all requests for temporary agency staff must include a business case for the panel to approve. A formal business case may be provided for larger spends.</p><p> </p><p>Consultancy does not have a central approval mechanism so this varies between the centre and the agencies as follows:</p><p> </p><p>DFT</p><p>A business case is always required.</p><p> </p><p>DVLA</p><p>A formal business case is always required for consultancy staff in the form of an Information and Communication Technology (ICT) spend approval.</p><p> </p><p>DVSA</p><p>Not all requests for consultancy and temporary staff are accompanied by a formal business case. The decision as to whether a formal business case is needed to accompany the request for consultancy and temporary staff is subject to value and circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>MCA</p><p>A formal business case is required for new consultancy spend over £50,000.</p><p> </p><p>VCA</p><p>A business case is always required.</p><p> </p><p>The Department complies with the appropriate Cabinet Office controls for consultancy expenditure and spending that exceeds the threshold may require additional detail in a business case.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T10:04:39.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756575/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756575/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756575/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756576","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Staff employed by our contractors are not able to access the Department for Transport’s IT systems without first agreeing to comply with our acceptable use policies. This places them under the same obligations to maintain the security and confidentiality of the Department’s information and systems as staff employed directly by the Department. They then receive the same communications and training on cyber security risks as our own staff, with those working in higher risk areas receiving a higher level of training.</p><p> </p><p>Where the Department’s sensitive information is processed by our contractors on their own systems, we require them to provide annual assurance that their staff and sub-contractors have received appropriate information security awareness training.</p><p> </p><p>DfT follows government procurement policy on cyber security. Contracts will contain appropriate confidentiality and security clauses where the service involves handling personal information and providing certain ICT products and services.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T11:48:51.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756576/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756576/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756576/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756577","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>HS2 Ltd fully accepts the findings and recommendations of the National Audit Office report on the 2016-17 redundancy scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The HS2 Ltd Board instructed the new Chief Executive of HS2 Ltd to ensure the situation described by the NAO cannot happen again. He has made a number of senior appointments in both HR and Finance to implement improvements to internal controls and governance arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>Additional controls are already in place on redundancy payments, while upgrades and improvements to the underlying staff and payroll systems are in development, and will be completed by May 2018.</p><p> </p><p>New governance arrangements are being agreed between the Department for Transport and HS2 Ltd to ensure all approvals processes and decisions are properly recorded and cascaded.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-12T07:47:42.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756577/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756577/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756577/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","High Speed Two: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Report of the Comptroller and Auditor General of the National Audit Office of 11 July 2017 on the 2016-17 Accounts of HS2 Ltd, whether HS2 Ltd's agreement to pay above approved levels for redundancy schemes has had consequences for the (a) structure, (b) management and (c) other aspects of that company.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756578","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Scotland Office has no plans to establish any new arms-length bodies.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:20:22.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756578/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756578/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756578/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Scotland Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756579","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>My Department has made no estimate on the number of new arms-length bodies we would establish once the UK has left the EU.</p><p> </p><p>While there are a number of agencies whose functions will transfer over to the UK, almost all of these will be absorbed into existing Government organisations.</p><p> </p><p>The Government policy ensures that new bodies are only set up as a last resort, when the core department or existing bodies are unable to carry out the proposed functions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-09-13T10:25:37.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756579/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756579/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756579/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-09-04","Northern Ireland Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756580","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Scotland Office do not currently have any temporary staff or consultants. Any such requests for consultancy or temporary staff would require a business case which would be subject to formal approval by the Senior Leadership Team.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:38:09.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756580/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756580/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756580/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Scotland Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756581","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Scotland Office does not have any consultancy assignments.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:38:57.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756581/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756581/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756581/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Scotland Office: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756582","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. Those that join do so on an assignment, loan or secondment from other Government bodies, principally the Ministry of Justice and the Scottish Government, who remain the employers. No information is held on the number of applications received for internal loans or secondments from Civil Servants since 2010.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:39:59.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756582/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756582/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756582/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Scotland Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756583","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Scotland Office is a small government department with limited property assets. As such, the department has not been commissioned to prepare a Strategic Asset Management Plan. Information about the department’s property interests is available in the Scotland Office Annual Report and Accounts and recorded on the Government Property Unit's property database (e-PIMS).</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:41:03.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756583/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756583/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756583/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Scotland Office: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756584","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Scotland Office do not currently have any temporary staff or consultants. Any such requests for consultancy or temporary staff would require formal approval by the Scotland Office Senior Leadership Team.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:41:52.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756584/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756584/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756584/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Scotland Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756585","Wales Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Wales Office is not an employer in its own right and does not hold this information. The Ministry of Justice carries out recruitment on our behalf and collates this information centrally.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-09-11T10:36:17.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756585/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756585/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756585/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-04","Wales Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756586","Wales Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Wales Office requires a formal business case to support requests for consultancy and temporary staff. A formal business case is not required for the short-term appointment of agency staff to business critical posts pending a permanent appointment being made.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-09-11T10:37:34.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756586/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756586/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756586/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-04","Wales Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756587","Wales Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Requests for consultancy and temporary staff would be considered by the Wales Office Board. The short-term appointment of agency staff to business critical posts may be approved by the Wales Office Director.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-09-11T10:38:48.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756587/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756587/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756587/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-04","Wales Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756588","Wales Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Wales Office uses Ministry of Justice policies and systems to procure consultancy services and does not pay daily rates for those services.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-09-11T10:39:37.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756588/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756588/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756588/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-04","Wales Office: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756589","Wales Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Wales Office is a government department with limited property assets. As such, the department has not been commissioned to prepare a Strategic Asset Management Plan.</p><p> </p><p>Information about the department’s property interests is available in the Wales Office Annual Report and Accounts and recorded on the Government Property Unit’s property database (e-PIMS).</p><p> </p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-09-12T09:52:31.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756589/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756589/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756589/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-04","Wales Office: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756590","Wales Office","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Wales Office has no plans to establish any new arms-length bodies.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-09-07T10:10:36.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756590/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756590/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756590/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-09-04","Wales Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756591","Women and Equalities","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Department has no plans to establish any new arms-length bodies once the UK has left the EU.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-09-14T16:32:19.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756591/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756591/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756591/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-09-04","Government Equalities Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what estimate she has made of the number of new arms-length bodies her Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756592","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>There is a central Departmental Approvals Committee (DAC) for the contingent labour framework which is used to recruit all temporary agency staff.</p><p> </p><p>Consultancy does not have a central approval mechanism; the Department and executive agencies have the following process:</p><p> </p><p>DFT</p><p>All consultancy approvals are obtained from the finance DAC panel.</p><p> </p><p>DVLA</p><p>All consultancy approvals are obtained via the ICT spend approval process.</p><p> </p><p>DVSA</p><p>Consultancy and temporary staff approvals are obtained from the People Committee or the Investment and Change Committee, depending on the circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>MCA</p><p>MCA records any consultancy expenditure over £10k on its central contract management system. All consultancy approvals for spend over £50,000 is delegated to the appropriate MCA board. No records for consultancy were identified.</p><p> </p><p>VCA</p><p>All consultancy approvals are obtained from the head of department, head of HR and CEO.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department also complies with the appropriate Cabinet Office controls for consultancy expenditure.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T11:43:18.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756592/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756592/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756592/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756593","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Strategic Asset Management Plans were first commissioned in 2014; the Department has submitted a Strategic Asset Management Plan to the Government Property Unit in each year since that date.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T11:45:59.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756593/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756593/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756593/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756594","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>This information is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-12T11:24:08.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756594/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756594/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756594/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Department for Transport: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756595","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The number of new arms-length bodies that will be required by the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy remains subject to a final assessment and is in part dependent on the outcome of negotiations with the EU.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:12:49.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756595/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756595/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756595/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756596","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy is committed to ensuring that contractors and their staff have a sound awareness of cyber risk matters and they take all necessary safeguards to protect the department’s information.</p><p>Where relevant, cyber security awareness, the need to ensure contractual compliance with Information Assurance standards such as ISO 27001:2013 certification and “Cyber Essentials/ Plus” is included in contract specifications and reviewed as part of the evaluation process. Contractors must comply with the department’s IT security policies and procedures.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-14T10:07:15.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756596/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756596/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756596/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756597","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-12","<p>As reported in the HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, the total amount paid to HMRC (Core department) and VOA (Agency) staff in exit packages was £27,482,000. The total paid to HMRC staff was £25,080,467. Of this figure, £8,488,638 was paid to men and £16,591,829 was paid to women. In 2016-17 98% of HMRC exits were voluntary.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-12T13:20:13.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756597/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756597/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756597/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Revenue and Customs: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 123 of the HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, how much of the £27,482,000 paid to HMRC staff in exit packages was paid to (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756598","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>Since 1 November 2016 the Department has released two employees, from current headcount circa 84,000 employees, under voluntary exit. The total compensation cost was £144,000. Both of these employees were men.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T14:35:04.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756598/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756598/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756598/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 13 July 2017 to Question 3369, how much of the £144,000 paid in exit packages to Department for Work and Pensions staff was paid to (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756599","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>At present, my Department has no plans to create any new arm’s-length bodies once the UK has left the EU.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-09-12T09:55:37.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756599/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756599/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756599/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756600","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government Property Unit first commissioned a Strategic Asset Management Plan for the Department in September 2014. The Department has submitted one in each of the years since.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T16:28:40.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756600/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756600/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756600/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756601","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>Yes, DWP gains assurance that a contractor is complying with obligations to deliver services in compliance with DWP’s security standards and policies through its industry standard contract management processes.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T16:25:49.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756601/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756601/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756601/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756602","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>All requests for consultancy and temporary staff were approved via a resource board.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T16:28:34.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756602/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756602/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756602/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756603","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>All requests for consultancy and temporary staff are accompanied by a formal business case.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T16:33:50.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756603/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756603/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756603/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756604","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department does not hold a central register of staff seconded into the Department, nor internal loans. Individuals seconded from an external organisation in to the Department do not have a Civil Service Contract and are not paid through the Departments payroll. <br></p><p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-11T14:40:41.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756604/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756604/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756604/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756605","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>Individual consultancy assignments can be paid in a number of different ways e.g. by project, weekly timesheets, by outputs, but essentially they are all based on daily rates.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T16:13:25.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756605/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756605/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756605/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756606","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>All contractors employed directly by DWP are expected to complete the DWP mandatory security e-learning and abide by the DWP Acceptable Use Policy if using DWP information and equipment. All contractors must undergo Baseline Personnel Security Standard Checks. DWP line managers are responsible for authorising IT access rights, ensuring contractors are aware of the AUP and completing a leavers checklist when the contractor leaves DWP.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-11T14:17:48.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756606/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756606/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756606/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will publish the criteria by which contractors demonstrate compliance with departmental security policies and standards.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756607","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>Since the Department’s creation, no strategic asset management plan has been submitted to the Government Property Unit. The Department currently does not directly own or hold the head-lease for any building.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-09-12T15:56:52.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756607/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756607/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756607/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756608","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to ensuring the best value for money when considering requests for consultancy and temporary staff. The Department has in place an approvals hierarchy by which all proposals for consultancy or temporary staff are reviewed and approved.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-09-12T15:54:04.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756608/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756608/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756608/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756609","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>All staff that have joined from other Government departments have been on a loan basis. The Department will not provide a running commentary on the number of applications received as recruitment is ongoing and our numbers are regularly changing. The Department now has over 450 staff, of which over 350 staff are on loan from across the Civil Service.</p><p>As a new department, the Department for Exiting the European Union is not in a position to report on the loans over the last 7 years.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-09-12T16:03:45.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756609/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756609/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756609/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756610","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union has not paid any consultancy assignments using a daily rate. Payment is based on project deliverables.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-09-12T16:01:13.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756610/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756610/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756610/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756611","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to ensuring the best value for money when considering requests for consultancy and temporary staff. The Department has in place an approvals hierarchy by which all proposals for consultancy or temporary staff are reviewed and approved, ensuring full commercial compliance and where necessary, the request will be accompanied by a business case.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-09-12T15:59:03.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756611/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756611/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756611/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756612","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy was created in July 2016. A strategic asset management plan is being developed for the new Department.</p><p>The Government Property Unit commissions Strategic Asset Management Plans from Departments on an annual basis.</p><p>Executive summaries of these plans will be published for the first time in autumn 2017.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:18:59.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756612/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756612/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756612/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756613","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) does not hold information on internal loans centrally.</p><p>In respect of secondments, BEIS has not received any applications for secondments from civil servants as secondments in to BEIS are only available to non-civil servants.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:20:26.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756613/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756613/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756613/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756614","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy does not have a resource board. Certain procurements for consultancy and temporary staff valued over £10k are required to have a procurement business case that requires approval by the Director of Human Resources amongst others.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:13:57.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756614/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756614/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756614/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756615","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) does not hold this information centrally although we believe the majority of our consultancy assignments to be paid at a daily rate. BEIS consultancy service requirements are sourced normally via the Crown Commercial Service ConsultancyOne framework which provides for charging based upon discounted supplier day rates.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:18:04.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756615/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756615/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756615/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756616","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>Major projects and programmes require formal business cases in accordance with HMT rules. Certain procurements for consultancy and temporary staff valued over £10k arising from these projects and programmes are required to have a formal approved (procurement) business case.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:15:08.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756616/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756616/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756616/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756617","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>In June 2016, the Department for International Trade brought together teams from the former UK Trade &amp; Investment and teams from the former Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the Cabinet Office, each with their own approvals regimes. Through a period of transition, including implementation of machinery of government changes, the department has established a coherent range of processes, governing the use of consultants and temporary staff which fit within the wider Cabinet Office Controls framework and these are kept under regular review. The processes depend on the nature of the work required, its duration, the value and the risk or complexity.</p><p>The Department endeavours to minimize the use of consultants. The proportion of any such consultancy assignments that are paid at a daily rate is not available as a metric.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","7936 ; 7957","2017-09-12T16:54:07.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756617/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756617/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756617/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756618","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>Since the department was formed in July 2016 we have had 2,591 applications from Civil Servants for advertised internal loan opportunities. We do not offer secondments internally within the Civil Service, as transfers of this nature happen on a loan basis.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-09-12T14:44:52.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756618/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756618/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756619","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department for International Trade was created on 13 July 2016 and therefore has not been required to submit a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-09-12T15:28:17.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756619/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756619/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756620","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>In June 2016, the Department for International Trade brought together teams from the former UK Trade &amp; Investment and teams from the former Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the Cabinet Office, each with their own approvals regimes. Through a period of transition, including implementation of machinery of government changes, the department has established a coherent range of processes, governing the use of consultants and temporary staff which fit within the wider Cabinet Office Controls framework and these are kept under regular review. The processes depend on the nature of the work required, its duration, the value and the risk or complexity.</p><p>The Department endeavours to minimize the use of consultants. The proportion of any such consultancy assignments that are paid at a daily rate is not available as a metric.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","7936 ; 7978","2017-09-12T16:54:07.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756620/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756620/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether requests for consultancy and temporary staff for the his Department must be accompanied by a formal business case.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756621","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>In June 2016, the Department for International Trade brought together teams from the former UK Trade &amp; Investment and teams from the former Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the Cabinet Office, each with their own approvals regimes. Through a period of transition, including implementation of machinery of government changes, the department has established a coherent range of processes, governing the use of consultants and temporary staff which fit within the wider Cabinet Office Controls framework and these are kept under regular review. The processes depend on the nature of the work required, its duration, the value and the risk or complexity.</p><p>The Department endeavours to minimize the use of consultants. The proportion of any such consultancy assignments that are paid at a daily rate is not available as a metric.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","7957 ; 7978","2017-09-12T16:54:07.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756621/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756621/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what proportion of consultancy assignments procured by his Department are paid at a daily rate.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756622","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>The UK’s relationship with the EU's agencies upon exit will be evaluated in light of delivering the twelve objectives outlined by the Prime Minister to achieve a deep and special partnership between the UK and the EU. The UK’s future relationship with the EU's decentralised bodies after leaving the EU is a matter for the negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for International Trade is in the process of developing its future UK trade policy.</p><p> </p><p>Prior to any decisions on establishing new agencies, the Government will always look to minimise disruption and costs.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-09-12T14:05:07.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756622/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756622/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756622/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756623","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-12","<p>The policy set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the National Cyber Security Strategy applies to everyone employed by the Department for International Trade, including contractors.</p><p>The Department for International Trade is committed to ensuring that contractors and their staff have a sound awareness of cyber risk matters and they take all necessary safeguards to protect the department’s information.</p><p>Cyber security awareness, the need to ensure contractual compliance with Information Assurance standards such as ISO 27001:2013 certification and “Cyber Essentials/ Plus” is included in contract specifications and reviewed as part of the evaluation process. Contractors must comply with the department’s IT security policies and procedures.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-09-12T15:23:30.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756623/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756623/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756623/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-04","Department for International Trade: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756624","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>Details of the number, type, compensation levels and cost of exits from The Department for Exiting the European Union are routinely published in the Department’s Annual Report and Accounts. As set out in the 16/17 accounts, the Department did not incur any redundancy costs in 2016-17. This information will continue to be published in future Annual Reports and Accounts for the Department.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-09-12T16:02:19.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756624/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756624/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756624/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 6 July 2017 to Question 3362, on redundancy, whether any staff from his Department have been made redundant.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756625","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Since its inception in September 2015, the GCS Knowledge &amp; Capability Unit has not seconded any staff members to foreign Governments and as such, no fees have been charged.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-11T11:13:03.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756625/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756625/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756625/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-04","Government Departments: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many secondments have been organised from the Government Communication Service to positions in which foreign Governments since the inception of that body.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756626","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-12","<p>The department has a mandatory Security Induction briefing for all staff and contractors which covers cyber risk and typical cyber attack vectors, how to report these and the appropriate preventative action to take. This is over and above the annual mandatory e-learning on responsible information handling that must be completed by all staff and contractors. Cyber security advice is also emphasised during IT deployment.</p><p>Our IT suppliers work with the security team to highlight cyber risks and maintain awareness on emerging cyber threats and mitigations. Our cyber team regularly present these to the board to maintain awareness at the highest level and send communications on suspected attacks e.g. spear phishing to all staff regularly.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-09-12T15:54:01.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756626/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756626/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756626/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756627","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-07","<p>The current cholera outbreak in Yemen has been declared by the UN as the worst in the world. Since the start of the outbreak in April, over 612,000 suspected cholera cases have been recorded and more than 2,000 deaths. Fewer than half of Yemen’s health facilities are functioning, and more than 19 million people have no access to clean water or sanitation.</p><p>In response, the UK increased aid to Yemen to £139 million for 2017-18, prioritising life-saving interventions including clean water and sanitation for an expected 1.2 million people. This also includes support to tackle the underlying causes of cholera by helping provide emergency food, nutrition, as well as supporting cholera prevention and providing medical supplies and treatment for those affected.</p><p>This is a significant increase from previous years, and makes us the second-largest contributors to the UN’s 2017 Yemen Appeal and the third-largest humanitarian donor overall. We are constantly reviewing our position and examining whether further funding should be made available, as we continue to work with the UN, other partners and donors to monitor and improve the response to the outbreak.</p><p>On the 11<sup>th</sup> August, the Secretary of State for International Development announced that we are targeting £8 million of our support to UNICEF and the International Organization for Migration on activities specifically to address cholera. The funding will be used to provide medical supplies to half a million people, give safe access to chlorinated water to 300,000 people, and rehabilitate medical facilities used by 250,000 people.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-07T13:20:59.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756627/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756627/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756627/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Yemen: Cholera","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the Government plans to increase funding available for the Yemen Humanitarian Response Plan to tackle the cholera outbreak in that country.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","8316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756628","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Government will in due course publish a Green Paper that will closely examine markets which are not working fairly for consumers.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-07T15:40:23.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756628/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756628/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756628/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Consumers: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when his Department plans to publish the Consumer Law Green Paper.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","7541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756629","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-12","<p>The government is committed to supporting investment in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>For example, in July the government launched the £400m Digital Infrastructure Investment Fund for investment in full fibre broadband across the country.</p><p> </p><p>The government is also consulting on whether to introduce a national investment fund to channel investment into fast growing firms and support economic growth.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the National Productivity Investment Fund announced by the Chancellor last year is providing an additional £23bn of investment in areas like housing, transport and digital infrastructure.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-09-12T10:48:11.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756629/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756629/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756629/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Sovereign Wealth Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department has taken to establish a national sovereign wealth fund.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756630","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>Following successful pilots of the ‘Trusted Partner’ scheme and the ‘Landlord Portal Service’, DWP will rollout both initiatives together.</p><p> </p><p>The Trusted Partner scheme allows social landlords to play a key role in engaging with their tenants who are Universal Credit claimants, helping those who can’t manage their housing payments to access the support available. The Landlord Portal provides social landlords with the ability to submit information directly to the Universal Credit online system, which supports timely and accurate payment of housing costs to Universal Credit claimants.</p><p> </p><p>The next stage of rollout for both initiatives means that all Trusted Partner landlords will have access to the Landlord Portal. We have already introduced this to the landlords involved in our Trusted Partner pilot. In the coming months, we will invite more social landlords in Universal Credit Full Service areas to enroll in the Landlord Portal, becoming Trusted Partners. The independent evaluation report of Trusted Partner will be published shortly.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","7855","2017-09-12T16:22:43.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756630/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756630/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756630/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress has been made on rolling out the Universal Credit Trusted Partner scheme; and whether he plans to publish an evaluation of the pilot for that scheme.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756631","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>Following successful pilots of the ‘Trusted Partner’ scheme and the ‘Landlord Portal Service’, DWP will rollout both initiatives together.</p><p> </p><p>The Trusted Partner scheme allows social landlords to play a key role in engaging with their tenants who are Universal Credit claimants, helping those who can’t manage their housing payments to access the support available. The Landlord Portal provides social landlords with the ability to submit information directly to the Universal Credit online system, which supports timely and accurate payment of housing costs to Universal Credit claimants.</p><p> </p><p>The next stage of rollout for both initiatives means that all Trusted Partner landlords will have access to the Landlord Portal. We have already introduced this to the landlords involved in our Trusted Partner pilot. In the coming months, we will invite more social landlords in Universal Credit Full Service areas to enroll in the Landlord Portal, becoming Trusted Partners. The independent evaluation report of Trusted Partner will be published shortly.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","7854","2017-09-12T16:22:43.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756631/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756631/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756631/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Universal Credit: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress his Department has made on developing the universal credit landlord portal; and what the roll-out schedule is for releasing that portal.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756632","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-08","<p>The assessment period and payment structure of Universal Credit creates a fixed period between date of entitlement and the first payment. Advances are available for people who are in financial need during the initial period before their first payment.</p><p>The Universal Credit Full Service digital system ensures that all agents and their managers are automatically aware in real time of any claimants on their caseload for whom a payment is due to be paid, or of any claimant for whom a payment will be due shortly, for which there are outstanding actions required.</p><p> </p><p>For Employment and Support Allowance and Jobseekers Allowance, the relevant computer system alerts staff in the event that any claim has not been processed and made ready for payment seven days after receipt of the claim. The target for processing a claim ready for payment is 10 days and, every day, the computer automatically produces a list of cases that are approaching that target to help ensure cases are put in payment on time.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-09-08T12:48:11.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756632/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756632/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756632/answer","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756632/answer/previousversion/8987","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will place in the Library a memorandum setting out in respect of (a) jobseeker's allowance, (b) employment and support allowance and (c) universal credit (i) those prompts within the computer system designed to alert staff to cases in which claimants are waiting more than 10 days for the determination of their claims and (ii) the circumstances in which those cases are reported to managers.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756633","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>Legal fees of defending the case in the High Court are £67,690. This figure includes VAT where payable (for example on Counsel’s fees) and disbursements but does not include costs attributable to time spent by Government advisory lawyers, as time spent by such advisory lawyers is not recorded in a manner that allows it to be attributable to individual court cases.</p><p> </p><p>DWP has also paid £125,000 (plus VAT) towards the Claimants’ costs.</p><p> </p><p>DWP’s legal costs for appealing the case in the Court of Appeal are estimated to be between £25,000 and £40,000 (this includes our best estimate of external Counsel fees).</p><p> </p><p>Evaluation of the previous cap level found capped households were <strong>41%</strong> more likely to go into work than similar uncapped households and lone parents affected by the cap were <strong>51%</strong> more likely to go into work than similar uncapped lone parents. It is a policy that has been shown to work and is saving the tax payer millions of pounds.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-11T14:07:39.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756633/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756633/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756633/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Social Security Benefits: Lone Parents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what cost to the public purse has been incurred by his Department (a) challenging and (b) appealing against the High Court ruling that lone parents with children aged under two should be exempt from the benefits cap.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","8309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756634","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>The Government intends to appoint an Anti-Corruption champion in due course.</p><p>The position of the Anti-Corruption Strategy remains the same as in the answer I gave to a smililar question on 27 June (PQ144); the Government is working on a new Anit-Corruption Strategy which will be published in due course.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-13T14:35:05.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756634/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756634/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756634/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-04","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the Government intends to (a) appoint an anti-corruption champion and (b) release its Anti-Corruption Strategy.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","8354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756635","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-07","<p>The responses to the call for evidence are currently being analysed and a response will be published in due course.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-07T14:09:43.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756635/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756635/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756635/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Foreign Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he plans to (a) publish the outcome of the Government's consultation and (b) introduce legislation on property ownership and public contracting by overseas companies and legal entities.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","8355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756636","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>Developing a workable and sustainable funding model for supported housing is a priority for the Government. We will set out further details on the Government’s plans in the autumn.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-11T14:18:20.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756636/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756636/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756636/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Supported Housing: Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will review plans to cap housing benefit at the local housing allowance rate for those living in supported housing.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","7571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756637","Department of Health","false","2017-09-11","<p>We have had no such discussions. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is responsible for determining whether its guidance should be updated following the publication of new evidence. NICE published technology appraisal guidance on the use of lumacaftor-ivacaftor (Orkambi) for the treatment of cystic fibrosis in July 2016. NICE plans to review its guidance to determine whether it should be updated in the light of any new evidence in 2019.</p><p> </p><p>If significant new evidence comes to light before the scheduled review date, NICE has processes in place to bring forward a review. NICE remains open to a further approach from the company, with new evidence or a revised price. Although there has been recent correspondence between NHS England and the company, NICE has not yet received any fresh proposals from the company.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-11T15:54:24.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756637/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756637/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756637/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-04","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with NICE on updating its final guidance on the use of Orkambi as a result of the scientific research published by Vertex at the North American Cystic Fibrosis Conference on 27 October 2016.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","7803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756638","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-09-08","<p>There are currently no routine discharges of raw sewage by water companies in England. Discharges from sewage treatment works must comply with permits issued under the Environmental Permitting Regulations (2010) by the Environment Agency. These permits are designed to protect the environment with the provision of sewage treatment to ensure compliance with relevant environmental directives such as the Bathing Water Directive and the Water Framework Directive. It is an offence for operators not to comply with their permit conditions.</p><p> </p><p>Discharges of raw sewage can occasionally occur during pollution incidents. Such incidents may happen if equipment breaks down or if there is damage to or blockages in the sewers allowing raw sewage to enter the environment. In such cases the Environment Agency is notified and the water company is required to mitigate the impact of the pollution. In the most serious cases the Environment Agency can take enforcement action, including prosecution or civil sanctions.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-09-08T13:43:53.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756638/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756638/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756638/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-09-04","Rivers: Sewage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to prevent the pollution of rivers by water companies through the disposal of raw sewage.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","7603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756639","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government recognises the need for debt sustainability, and for effective debt restructuring processes where a country can no longer repay its debts. The UK engages in discussions on debt internationally and agreed to principles on debt sustainability at the G20 earlier this year. We are also committed to apply the OECD sustainable lending principles domestically. However, the Government isn’t currently planning to introduce legislation related to UN Conference on Trade and Development principles on responsible lending and borrowing.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-09-12T10:56:29.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756639/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756639/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756639/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Overseas Loans: Developing Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will introduce legislation to enshrine the UN Conference on Trade and Development principles on responsible lending and borrowing in UK law.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","7539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756640","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>Energy suppliers are required by their licence to be party to the industry governance groups that oversee the relevant codes of practice (for gas: Meter Asset Managers’ Code of Practice (MAMCoP) and electricity: Meter Operators Code of Practice Agreement (MOCOPA)). The industry groups oversee compliance and can escalate issues to Ofgem, who can apply their usual range of enforcement powers for a licence breach.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, companies are required to comply with the conditions set out in the Waste Electric and Electronic Equipment (WEEE) Directive, which covers metering equipment.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","7800","2017-09-11T13:17:29.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756640/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756640/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756640/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what mechanisms Ofgem has to enforce its code of practice on removal of gas and electric meters.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756641","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department has not received any representations to amend the Smart Energy Code to include obligations with regards to the removal and recycle of legacy meters.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-09-12T16:00:37.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756641/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756641/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756641/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what representations he has received on including obligations to remove and recycle legacy gas and electric meters which were replaced during the Smart Energy roll-out on energy companies as part of the Smart Energy Code.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756642","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>No assessment has been made. We understand that some Meter Asset Providers (MAPs) are making refurbished meters available to countries who at present do not intend to install smart meters.</p><p>The roll-out of smart meters is an important national modernisation programme that will bring major benefits to consumers and the nation as a whole. Domestic customers will be offered an In-Home Display (IHD) enabling them to see what energy they are using and how much it is costing. Smart meters will also bring an end to estimated billing, transform the prepayment experience, and in time make switching energy suppliers easier and faster.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-09-12T15:59:20.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756642/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756642/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756642/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the potential export market available to UK firms who refurbish gas and electric meters that are no longer required in the UK because of smart meter roll-out; and what steps his Department is taking to help develop that market.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756643","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Existing obligations in relation to the removal, recycling and disposal of traditional gas and electricity meters apply for the smart meter rollout.</p><p> </p><p>Companies have responsibilities under the Waste Electric and Electronic Equipment (WEEE) Directive. The WEEE Directive implements the principle of “extended producer responsibility”. Under this principle, producers are required to take financial responsibility for the environmental impact of the products that they place on the market, specifically when those products become waste. It seeks to reduce the amount of such waste going to landfill by encouraging separate collection and subsequent treatment, re-use, recovery, recycling and environmentally sound disposal.</p><p> </p><p>Large suppliers involved in the smart meter rollout have developed their own strategies for the safe recycling or disposal of gas and electricity meters. Gas and electricity meters are refurbished and refitted where possible or ultimately recycled in line with manufacturer guidelines.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","7799","2017-09-11T13:14:25.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756643/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756643/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756643/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what obligation the energy industry has to remove, recycle and dispose of legacy gas and electric meters as part of the smart meter roll-out.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756644","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-13","<p>No estimate has been made as to the number of gas and electric meters replaced during the smart meter rollout that are either sent to landfill, or refurbished and reused. However, reports for the amount of Electrical and Electronic Equipment (EEE) placed on the market and collected in the UK under the Waste Electrical and Electronic Equipment Regulations are available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/waste-electrical-and-electronic-equipment-weee-in-the-uk" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/waste-electrical-and-electronic-equipment-weee-in-the-uk</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to ensuring that every home and small business in the country is offered a smart meter the end of 2020. Overall, the roll-out is set to deliver significant net benefits to consumers, estimated at £5.7 billion over the lifetime of the Programme, yielding £1.5 of savings for every £1 spent.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","7798","2017-09-13T14:13:23.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756644/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756644/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756644/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the number of gas and electric meters replaced during the smart energy roll-out that are (a) sent to landfill and (b) refurbished and reused.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7797"
