"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756761","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-11","<p>It is vital that offenders leaving prison are supported to lead successful and law-abiding lives in the community. That is why weIn 2014/15 the government reformed the probation system to strengthen its focus on reducing reoffending and protecting communities, and much progress has been made in implementing these reforms. For the first time around 40,000 offenders a year released from custodial sentences of less than 12 months are entitled to statutory support from probation on release, and new through-the-gate services have been introduced to improve the resettlement of released prisoners in the community. reformed the probation system to extend post-release supervision to all prisoners released from custody and introduce new through-the-gate resettlement services.</p><p>The Cheshire and Greater Manchester CRC provides support to offenders released from prisons in Greater Manchester. We understand that the current delivery of through-the-gate service across England and Wales must improve and recognise the issues raised by Her Majesty’s Chief Inspectors of Prisons and Probation in their report published in June. We are working with providers to explore improvements that could be made to the delivery of rehabilitative services, and we continue to hold providers rigorously to account for their performance to ensure they deliver services which reduce re-offending, protect the public and help offenders contribute to society.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-09-11T16:41:12.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756761/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756761/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Prisoners' Release: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he has made an assessment of the adequacy of rehabilitation and support services available to people leaving prison in Greater Manchester for the last two years.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756762","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>The latest available data on volumes of appeals, volumes overturned and volumes upheld can be found in quarterly published statistics from the Ministry of Justice in tables SSCS.1 and SSCS.3 of: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics#history" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics#history</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","8150","2017-09-12T12:55:05.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756762/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756762/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756762/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Personal Independence Payment: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many personal independence payment assessment appeals were taken to the tribunal stage in (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2017-18 to date.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756763","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>The latest available data on volumes of appeals, volumes overturned and volumes upheld can be found in quarterly published statistics from the Ministry of Justice in tables SSCS.1 and SSCS.3 of: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics#history" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics#history</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","8151","2017-09-12T12:55:05.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756763/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756763/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756763/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Personal Independence Payment: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many personal independence payment assessment decisions were (a) overturned as a result of an appeal tribunal and (b) maintained in (i) 2016-17 and (ii) 2017-18 to date.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756764","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>The table below shows the number of individuals in Salford and Eccles constituency who were previously in receipt of Disability Living Allowance (DLA) and who underwent a Personal Independence Payment (PIP) Reassessment between 6th April 2016 and 31st October 2016 resulting in either a reduced reward or removal of award.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Re-assessment Outcome</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong> <strong>Apr 6<sup>th</sup> to Oct 31<sup>st</sup> 2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Award Decreased</p></td><td><p>190</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Disallowed post referral to the AP</p></td><td><p>160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Disallowed pre referral to the AP</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Withdrawn</p></td><td><p>#</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>380</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>October 2016 is the latest published data available. Later data is available on DWP systems but has been withheld as it will be published as part of official statistics in December 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Figures have been rounded to the nearest 10. ‘#’ indicates a total of less than 5. Columns may not sum due to rounding.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-09-12T11:57:15.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756764/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756764/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756764/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Personal Independence Payment: Salford and Eccles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Salford and Eccles constituency had personal independence payment awards reduced or removed in (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2017-18 to date as a result of reassessment.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756765","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Large and Medium-sized Companies and Groups (Accounts and Reports) Regulations 2008, as amended in 2013, already require quoted companies to disclose remuneration received by directors as a result of the achievement of annual performance measures.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-07T14:03:59.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756765/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756765/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756765/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Directors: Incentives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper, Corporate Governance Reform, published on 29 August 2017, whether companies will be required to make a full disclosure of executive bonus payments and how they are paid.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756766","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>Work is underway to bring forward legislative proposals for pay ratio reporting as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p>The pay ratio reporting requirement is intended to apply to the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of the company and to be determined by reference to the single figure for total remuneration receivable by the CEO that quoted companies are required to disclose annually (along with the pay of other directors).</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","8199","2017-09-12T07:47:52.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756766/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756766/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756766/answer","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756766/answer/previousversion/8978","Biography information for Margot James","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper, Corporate Governance Reform, published on 29 August 2017, whether the publication of pay multiples will apply solely to the CEO of a company.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756767","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>Work is underway to bring forward legislative proposals for pay ratio reporting as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p>The pay ratio reporting requirement is intended to apply to the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of the company and to be determined by reference to the single figure for total remuneration receivable by the CEO that quoted companies are required to disclose annually (along with the pay of other directors).</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","8198","2017-09-12T07:47:52.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756767/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756767/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756767/answer","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756767/answer/previousversion/8979","Biography information for Margot James","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper, Corporate Governance Reform, published on 29 August 2017, whether annual pay ratio reporting will require the reporting of exact pay and remuneration.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756768","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Work is underway to bring forward legislative proposals as soon as possible to require companies to disclose their corporate governance arrangements.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T13:11:47.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756768/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756768/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756768/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Company Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 42 of the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to require companies to disclose their corporate governance arrangements.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756769","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Government’s green paper on corporate governance reform sought views on the option of designating a non-executive director to ensure that voices of employees and other interested groups are heard at board level. Responses to the consultation suggested that this could be an effective option if appropriately resourced and supported, and care taken to ensure that the responsibilities associated with the role are clearly identified.</p><p> </p><p>It will be for individual boardrooms to determine how they can engage most effectively with employees and meet their duty to have regard to employee interests.</p><p> </p><p>The Government intends to introduce secondary legislation to require all companies of significant size (private as well as public) to explain how their directors comply with the requirements of section 172 to have regard to employee and other interests.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","8174","2017-09-11T13:09:45.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756769/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756769/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756769/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, what plans he has to require companies to accept recommendations from an employee advisory council.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756770","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave to Questions UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-09-04/8198/" target="_blank">8198</a> and <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-09-04/8199/" target="_blank">8199</a>.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-12T15:35:07.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756770/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756770/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756770/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 20 of the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to require quoted companies to report the ratio of CEO pay to the average pay of their UK workforce.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756771","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>Of the 375 respondents to the Corporate Governance Reform green paper consultation, 25 supported option (iii) which would require or encourage quoted company pay policies to set an upper threshold for total annual pay and ensure a binding vote where annual remuneration exceeds that threshold. None of the trade unions responding to the consultation supported this option.</p><p> </p><p>Of the 375 respondents to the consultation, 26 supported option (iv) which would require the existing binding vote on executive pay policies to be held more frequently than every three years (or give shareholders the option of bringing forward an earlier binding vote). One trade union and one trade union representative council supported option (iv) representing 8% of the respondents who supported this option.</p><p> </p><p>Of the 375 respondents to the consultation, 76 supported an annual binding shareholder vote on some or all elements of executive remuneration. This included two trade unions and one trade union representative council, comprising 4% of the respondents who supported this option.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","8180","2017-09-11T13:06:12.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756771/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756771/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756771/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to paragraph 1.6 of the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, how many and what proportion of the respondents that supported an annual binding vote on remuneration were trade unions.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756772","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>Of the 375 respondents to the Corporate Governance Reform green paper consultation, 25 supported option (iii) which would require or encourage quoted company pay policies to set an upper threshold for total annual pay and ensure a binding vote where annual remuneration exceeds that threshold. None of the trade unions responding to the consultation supported this option.</p><p> </p><p>Of the 375 respondents to the consultation, 26 supported option (iv) which would require the existing binding vote on executive pay policies to be held more frequently than every three years (or give shareholders the option of bringing forward an earlier binding vote). One trade union and one trade union representative council supported option (iv) representing 8% of the respondents who supported this option.</p><p> </p><p>Of the 375 respondents to the consultation, 76 supported an annual binding shareholder vote on some or all elements of executive remuneration. This included two trade unions and one trade union representative council, comprising 4% of the respondents who supported this option.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","8179","2017-09-11T13:06:12.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756772/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756772/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756772/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Company Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to paragraph 1.7 of the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, how many and what proportion of the respondents that supported options (iii) and (iv) were trade unions.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756773","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-07","<p>The register will bring together publicly available data on quoted companies’ shareholder voting records and any actions taken by companies to address significant shareholder dissent on individual resolutions. As the representative body for a large proportion of the UK’s investment community which votes on such resolutions, the Investment Association is well placed to establish and maintain the register.</p><p> </p><p>In its response to the Government’s green paper consultation on Corporate Governance Reform the Investment Association set out its intention to maintain a public register of quoted companies that experience significant shareholder dissent on executive remuneration resolutions.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-07T14:00:46.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756773/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756773/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756773/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper, Corporate Governance Reform, published on 29 August 2017, what representations he has received on the proposal for the Investment Association to maintain a public register of listed companies that experience shareholder opposition to pay awards.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756774","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government is committed to strengthening the worker voice in the boardroom. My Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State had one meeting specifically on the subject of corporate governance with trade union representatives at a roundtable event held in the Department on 6 February 2017. In addition, the Secretary of State and his Ministerial team met regularly with representatives of the trade unions during the preparation of the paper. This included a Trade Unions Congress chaired roundtable on the Industrial Strategy, attended by the heads of the six main unions, on 18 April 2017 where Corporate Governance was discussed.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-12T15:28:50.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756774/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756774/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756774/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, how many meetings he or ministers of his Department had with representative of trade unions during the preparation of that paper.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756775","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-09-04/8196/" target="_blank">8196</a>.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-12T15:29:44.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756775/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756775/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756775/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Business: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, for what reason the Financial Conduct Authority will not maintain a register of listed companies that experienced shareholder opposition to pay awards.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756776","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Government’s green paper on corporate governance reform sought views on the option of designating a non-executive director to ensure that voices of employees and other interested groups are heard at board level. Responses to the consultation suggested that this could be an effective option if appropriately resourced and supported, and care taken to ensure that the responsibilities associated with the role are clearly identified.</p><p> </p><p>It will be for individual boardrooms to determine how they can engage most effectively with employees and meet their duty to have regard to employee interests.</p><p> </p><p>The Government intends to introduce secondary legislation to require all companies of significant size (private as well as public) to explain how their directors comply with the requirements of section 172 to have regard to employee and other interests.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","8177","2017-09-11T13:09:45.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756776/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756776/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756776/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Directors: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 4 of the Government's paper Corporate Governance Reform published on 29 August 2017, whether he has assessed the potential effect of a designated non-executive director on strengthening the voice of employee influence.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756777","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>The detriment to retail energy customers on poor value standard variable tariffs, which was identified by the Competition and Markets Authority as averaging £1.4bn a year, must be addressed.</p><p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has written to the Chief Executive of Ofgem asking him to advise on what action the regulator intends to take to safeguard consumers on the poorest value tariffs and to consider the future of standard variable tariffs. The Secretary of State will consider further action in the light of Ofgem’s proposals and remains prepared to legislate if necessary.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T16:40:56.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756777/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756777/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756777/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if it is the Government's policy to bring forward legislative proposals to introduce an energy price cap.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756778","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-07","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State has written to the Chief Executive of Ofgem asking him to advise on what action the regulator intends to take to safeguard consumers on the poorest value tariffs and to consider the future of standard variable tariffs. The Secretary of State will assess whether further action is necessary once he receives Ofgem’s proposals.</p><p> </p><p>Ofgem already have extensive powers which would allow them to establish a price cap on household energy prices, but new legislation would be required in order to oblige Ofgem to put such a cap in place. The Secretary of State remains prepared to legislate if necessary.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-07T13:55:42.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756778/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756778/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756778/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-04","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether legislation is required to implement the Government's proposed cap on household energy prices.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","8440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756779","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The performance indicators agreed with National Savings and Investments for the delivery of Tax-Free childcare cover a range of areas including customer experience, payment processing, and sign-up.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-09-11T15:20:56.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756779/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756779/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756779/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the performance indicators are which he has agreed with National Savings and Investments for the delivery of tax-free childcare.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","7777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756780","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>As of 6 September 2017, 115,198 parents had successfully applied through the childcare service for 30 hours free childcare; over 25,404 parents had successfully applied for tax-free childcare; and 100,113 parents had successfully applied for both 30 hours free childcare and Tax-Free Childcare.</p><p> </p><p>As Minister of State at the Department for Education, Robert Goodwill, told the House on 6 September 2017, as of 31 August 216,384 eligibility codes had been issued for 3 year olds that were valid for the September term.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-09-11T15:09:21.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756780/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756780/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756780/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many parents have successfully signed up for (a) 30-hours free childcare, (b) tax-free childcare and (c) both 30-hours free childcare and tax-free childcare.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","7789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756781","Department for Education","false","2017-09-12","<p>The UK greatly values its relationship with Cuba and signed a Memorandum of Understanding in April 2016, with the aim of enhancing co-operation in higher education. We are committed to the principles of partnership and development as set out in the Memorandum.</p><p> </p><p>We are aware of the interest around this issue and, at the request of the Open University, officials from the Department for Education, the Department for International Trade, and the Foreign and Commonwealth Office have met with it to discuss its use of a restricted countries list in its application process, in particular in relation to Cuba.</p><p> </p><p>There are no UK or EU sanctions against Cuba. However, we understand that private organisations such as the Open University have to take decisions about their exposure to sanctions on the basis of commercial considerations, their own legal advice and appropriate risk assessments.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-09-12T11:58:55.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756781/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756781/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756781/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-04","Open University: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what representations her Department has received on the Open University's refusal to accept students from Cuba.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","7842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756782","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>This country has an excellent national road safety record and the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) regularly reviews the delivery of the driving test to ensure the test is relevant and appropriate to real life driving on Great Britain’s roads, irrespective of our membership of the EU.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-11T12:42:20.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756782/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756782/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756782/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to review the driving test after the UK leaves the EU and is no longer subject to the European Driving Licence Directive.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","7805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756783","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) is confident that the training and testing of practical test candidates adequately covers the ability to interact safely with all road users, including heavy goods vehicles (HGV).</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the National Standards for Driving, the Highway Code and ‘The Official DVSA Guide to Driving: the essential skills’ make specific reference to large vehicles, highlighting that HGVs:</p><ul><li>need for more room to manoeuvre;</li><li>travel at slower speeds; and</li><li>can block the view of other drivers.</li></ul><p> </p><p>They also highlight that drivers of large vehicles might not be able to see other road users in their mirrors and give guidance on how to overtake a large vehicle safely.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-11T09:50:17.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756783/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756783/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756783/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to introduce a mandatory element to the driving test on driving safely in the presence of heavy goods vehicles.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","7804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756784","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-08","<p>The Defence Science and Technology Laboratory (Dstl) at Porton Down, Wiltshire, is licensed by the Home Office to conduct the Ministry of Defence's in-house research involving the use of animals.</p><p>The majority of the animals used at Dstl are employed in the development of new vaccines, treatments or medical procedures. Every procedure is undertaken in strict accordance with the terms of the Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986. Alternatives to avoid animal testing are considered during the outset of the design of each research programme.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","7866","2017-09-08T13:36:14.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756784/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756784/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756784/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Porton Down: Animal Experiments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether animal testing is conducted at Porton Down.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","7776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756785","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-08","<p>The Defence Science and Technology Laboratory (Dstl) at Porton Down, Wiltshire, is licensed by the Home Office to conduct the Ministry of Defence's in-house research involving the use of animals.</p><p>The majority of the animals used at Dstl are employed in the development of new vaccines, treatments or medical procedures. Every procedure is undertaken in strict accordance with the terms of the Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986. Alternatives to avoid animal testing are considered during the outset of the design of each research programme.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","7776","2017-09-08T13:36:14.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756785/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756785/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756785/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Ministry of Defence: Animal Experiments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will prohibit animal testing at his Department's facilities.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","7866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756786","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>DFID’s programme in Burma has an allocated budget of £94 million for financial year 2017/18 and £100 million for financial year 2018/19. Information on individual projects is available on the DFID Development Tracker (www.devtracker.dfid.gov.uk).</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-11T17:01:27.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756786/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756786/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756786/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Burma: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the amount of resources from the foreign aid budget that will be allocated to projects in Burma in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018; and if she will list those projects.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","8284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756787","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-11","<p>In financial year 2015/16 DFID Burma’s programme totalled £100 million and in 2016/17 it was £99 million. Information on individual projects is available on the DFID Development Tracker (www.devtracker.dfid.gov.uk).</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-11T17:01:05.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756787/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756787/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756787/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-04","Burma: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much funding from the foreign aid budget was allocated to projects in Burma in (a) 2015 and (b) 2016; and if she will list those projects.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","8283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756788","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer provided at UIN HC4957 for information about the effectiveness and use of the new business rates appeals system, Check, Challenge, and Appeal.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","8323","2017-09-07T14:11:59.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756788/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756788/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756788/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the new business rates appeal process known as check, challenge, appeal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","8321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756789","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-07","<p>The number of proposals against the 2010 Rating List received by Valuation Office Agency in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2016-17 are shown in the attached table.</p><p>These numbers are consistent with the Official Statistics on Non Domestic Rating Challenges and Changes released by the Valuation Office Agency on 24 August 2017.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-07T14:30:34.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756789/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756789/answer","Annex - NDR_CC LRW1_yearly_figures_as_at_3006217_v3 (002).docx","2010 Local Rating List ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756789/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many businesses appealed their business rates in each of the last seven years in (a) England, (b) each English region and (c) each local authority area.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","8322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756790","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer provided at UIN HC4957 for information about the effectiveness and use of the new business rates appeals system, Check, Challenge, and Appeal.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","8321","2017-09-07T14:11:59.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756790/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756790/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756790/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many businesses have registered to use the new business rates appeal process since the check, challenge, appeal system was established in (a) England, (b) each English region and (c) each local authority area.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","8323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756791","Home Office","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Dublin Regulation allows unaccompanied children who have claimed asylum in another Member State to be transferred here to have their asylum claim assessed if they have a qualifying family member legally present in the UK and transfer would be in their best interests. In order for the Dublin Regulation to apply, an unaccompanied child must first claim asylum in the Member State in which they are located and that Member State must issue a Take Charge Request to the UK.</p><p>The Government has committed to publishing regular updates on the number of unaccompanied asylum seeking children transferred to the UK from Europe. This data will be published in the coming months.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on transfers under the Dublin Regulation are already available here:</p><p><a href="http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Asylum_quarterly_report" target="_blank">http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Asylum_quarterly_report</a></p><p> </p><p>Asylum statistics are published quarterly in the Home Office Immigration Statistics release, which can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/how-many-people-do-we-grant-asylum-or-protection-to" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/how-many-people-do-we-grant-asylum-or-protection-to</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-07T16:17:59.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756791/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756791/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many children have been transferred to the UK under the Dublin III Regulation since January 2017; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Williams","Stockton South","Dr Paul Williams","8318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756792","Home Office","false","2017-09-07","<p>At present we do not publish data on cases covered by the Dublin Regulation. Eurostat, the EU’s statistics agency, regularly publishes Member State figures, which can be found at:</p><p><a href="http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Dublin_statistics_on_countries_responsible_for_asylum_application" target="_blank">http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Dublin_statistics_on_countries_responsible_for_asylum_application</a></p><p>The Government has committed to publishing regular updates on the number of unaccompanied asylum seeking children transferred to the UK from Europe, including those transferred under the Dublin Regulation. This data will be published in the coming months.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-07T16:16:17.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756792/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756792/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756792/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-04","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the number of children is who were transferred under the Dublin III Regulation in 2016 by nature of the relative they were reunited with.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Williams","Stockton South","Dr Paul Williams","8317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756793","Department for Education","false","2017-09-12","<p>The government has set up a £5m fund to help celebrate this important occasion.</p><p> </p><p>Officials in the Government Equalities Office are responsible for this fund. The funding will be available for projects in England, and details including application criteria will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p><p>The Barnett formula has been applied to this funding in the usual way and it is for the devolved administrations, including the Welsh Government, to decide whether, and how, they choose to mark the centenary.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-09-12T16:59:28.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756793/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756793/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756793/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-09-04","Representation of the People Act 1918: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if her Department will be responsible for the administration of the 1918 Representation of the People commemoration fund; and if she will publish details on how organisations can apply for grants from that fund.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","7590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756794","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The numbers of cadets that have completed gliding courses and been awarded wings in each of the last five years are as follows:</p><p>2013 - 11,748</p><p>2014 - 1,705</p><p>2015 - 53</p><p>2016 - 142</p><p>2017 - 741</p><p>In 2013 and 2014 these courses were across all Volunteer Gliding Squadrons (VGS). In 2015 and 2016 these were with Central Gliding School (CGS) Syerston. In 2017 in addition to CGS, these also include courses with the three VGS that have returned to flight, 637VGS at Little Rissington, 644VGS at Syerston and 635VGS at Topcliffe.</p><p>Prior to the gliding pause, which commenced in Apr 2014, there were circa 560 qualified gliding instructors spread over the VGS. Many of these gliding instructors are undertaking ground duties while awaiting completion of their 'return to flying' package. This includes instructing groundschool topics and on the Part Task Trainers which are our ground based simulators.</p><p>61 instructors have now completed their 'return to flying' package and regained their gliding instructional qualifications to deliver airborne training to cadets.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7853","2017-09-12T16:25:09.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756794/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756794/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756794/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Air Force: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many and what proportion of air cadets have completed courses in gliding in each of the last five years; how many air cadets have completed gliding courses in each of the volunteer gliding squadrons since 2014; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","7851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756795","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>We do not record the numbers of Air Cadets that join or leave per year. However, we publish statistics on the total number of air cadets in both the Air Training Corps and Combined Cadet Force (RAF) sections. For the last five years the total number of cadets in both organisations combined is as follows:</p><p>2017 - 39,020</p><p>2016 - 40,750</p><p>2015 - 41,430</p><p>2014 - 42,280</p><p>2013 - 42,920</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-12T16:35:16.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756795/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756795/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756795/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Air Force: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many young people have (a) joined and (b) left the air cadets in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","7852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756796","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The numbers of cadets that have completed gliding courses and been awarded wings in each of the last five years are as follows:</p><p>2013 - 11,748</p><p>2014 - 1,705</p><p>2015 - 53</p><p>2016 - 142</p><p>2017 - 741</p><p>In 2013 and 2014 these courses were across all Volunteer Gliding Squadrons (VGS). In 2015 and 2016 these were with Central Gliding School (CGS) Syerston. In 2017 in addition to CGS, these also include courses with the three VGS that have returned to flight, 637VGS at Little Rissington, 644VGS at Syerston and 635VGS at Topcliffe.</p><p>Prior to the gliding pause, which commenced in Apr 2014, there were circa 560 qualified gliding instructors spread over the VGS. Many of these gliding instructors are undertaking ground duties while awaiting completion of their 'return to flying' package. This includes instructing groundschool topics and on the Part Task Trainers which are our ground based simulators.</p><p>61 instructors have now completed their 'return to flying' package and regained their gliding instructional qualifications to deliver airborne training to cadets.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7851","2017-09-12T16:25:09.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756796/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756796/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756796/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Armed Forces: Gliding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many instructors qualified to conduct gliding lessons through the Volunteer Gliding Squadrons have been available to offer lessons in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","7853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756797","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>​​The UK does not have its own domestic sanctions regime but does act with the international community to implement UN and EU sanctions such as those on the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. We will continue working with partners, including EU Member States and those in the region, to consider a wide range of options, including sanctions.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-12T15:45:33.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756797/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756797/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-04","Venezuela: Sanctions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will impose sanctions on President Maduro and other high-ranking Venezuelan Government officials.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","7601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756798","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-20","<p>On 23 February 2017 the Government published details of reforms relating to road traffic accident-related personal injury claims in its response to the ‘Reforming the Soft Tissue Injury (‘whiplash’) Claims Process consultation - https://consult.justice.gov.uk/digital-communications/reforming-soft-tissue-injury-claims/, which sets out reforms to increase the small claims track limit for road traffic accident related personal injury claims to £5,000, and for all other personal injury claims to £2,000.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-09-20T15:29:19.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756798/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756798/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756798/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-04","Small Claims: Personal Injury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he has plans to bring forward legislative proposals to increase the small claims limit for road traffic accident-related personal injury claims to £5,000 and to increase the small claims limit for all other personal injury claims to £2,000.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","7819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756799","Ministry of Defence","true","2017-09-07","<p>Data on the outcomes of Royal Military Police investigations over the last ten years will take time to collate. Information relating to disciplinary action is currently <del class="ministerial">unlkown</del><ins class="ministerial">unavailable</ins>. I will write shortly to provide the data requested.</p><p>The Army does not tolerate unacceptable behaviour by any personnel, including staff and Junior Soldiers at the Army Foundation College, in any form. All allegations are treated very seriously and investigated. As part of our duty of care, instructors at the College will normally be suspended until an investigation has been carried out, or depending on the circumstances, they may be removed from post without prejudice and reassigned. As a result of the misconduct investigation and findings, the without prejudice removal will then be classified as blameworthy or non-blameworthy, and dealt with accordingly.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-07T16:54:31.543Z","2017-09-08T10:39:58.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756799/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756799/answer","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756799/answer/previousversion/8920","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army Foundation College","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Military Police investigations into staff at AFC Harrogate there have been in the last 10 years; what the (a) related allegations and (b) outcomes were in each of those investigations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756800","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The table below shows the number of Army applicants between 1 January (the start of the ‘This is Belonging’ campaign) and 31 August 2017 aged between 16 and 24 on application.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Regular</p></td><td><p>Regualr</p></td><td><p>Reserve</p></td><td><p>Reserve</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Officer</p></td><td><p>Soldier</p></td><td><p>Officer</p></td><td><p>Soldier</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aged 16-24 years</p></td><td><p>5,280</p></td><td><p>35,160</p></td><td><p>1,850</p></td><td><p>13,730</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes</p><p> </p><p>This question has been answered using information held in recruiting data. Figures provided are a single service estimate and are not official statistics.</p><p> </p><p>An applicant has been defined as someone who has applied and their data has been loaded onto the recruitment database.</p><p> </p><p>Reserves figures are for Group A Reserves. These are Reserves who are recruited through the National Recruiting Centre and are available for employment on specific tasks at home and overseas.</p><p> </p><p>Numbers have been rounded to the nearest 10. Numbers ending in five have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-12T13:55:41.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756800/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756800/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people have applied to join the Army who are aged between 16 and 24 since the commencement of the This is Belonging campaign.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756801","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-07","<p>Data on the outcomes of Royal Military Police investigations over the last ten years will take time to collate. Information relating to disciplinary action is currently unlkown. I will write shortly to provide the data requested.</p><p> </p><p>The Army does not tolerate unacceptable behaviour by any personnel, including staff and Junior Soldiers at the Army Foundation College, in any form. All allegations are treated very seriously and investigated. As part of our duty of care, instructors at the College will normally be suspended until an investigation has been carried out, or depending on the circumstances, they may be removed from post without prejudice and reassigned. As a result of the misconduct investigation and findings, the without prejudice removal will then be classified as blameworthy or non-blameworthy, and dealt with accordingly.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7890 ; 7892","2017-09-07T16:54:31.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756801/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756801/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army Foundation College","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many instructors have been returned to unit from AFC Harrogate (a) with and (b) without prejudice in the last 10 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756802","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-07","<p>Data on the outcomes of Royal Military Police investigations over the last ten years will take time to collate. Information relating to disciplinary action is currently unlkown. I will write shortly to provide the data requested.</p><p> </p><p>The Army does not tolerate unacceptable behaviour by any personnel, including staff and Junior Soldiers at the Army Foundation College, in any form. All allegations are treated very seriously and investigated. As part of our duty of care, instructors at the College will normally be suspended until an investigation has been carried out, or depending on the circumstances, they may be removed from post without prejudice and reassigned. As a result of the misconduct investigation and findings, the without prejudice removal will then be classified as blameworthy or non-blameworthy, and dealt with accordingly.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7890 ; 7891","2017-09-07T16:54:31.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756802/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756802/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army Foundation College: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many disciplinary investigations into instructors have been conducted at AFC Harrogate in the last 10 years; what the (a) related allegations and (b) outcomes were in each of those investigations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756803","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister of State for the Armed Forces (Mr Lancaster) on 5 September 2017 to Questions 6675 and 6676.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","7743","2017-09-12T13:50:07.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756803/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756803/answer","20170905_WQnA_extract_on_Army_Recruitment.docx","6675 - WQnA extract on Army Recruitment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756803/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the This is Belonging campaign by the Army was specifically marketed to 16 to 24-year olds in low socio-economic groups.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756804","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-12","<p>The table below shows the number of Army applicants between 1 January (the start of the ‘This is Belonging’ campaign) and 31 August 2017 broken down by gender.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Regular</p></td><td><p>Regular</p></td><td><p>Reserve</p></td><td><p>Reserve</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Officer</p></td><td><p>Soldier</p></td><td><p>Officer</p></td><td><p>Soldier</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>6,840</p></td><td><p>39,710</p></td><td><p>3,240</p></td><td><p>22,050</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>2,600</p></td><td><p>8,350</p></td><td><p>1,380</p></td><td><p>6,400</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes</p><p> </p><p>This question has been answered using information held in recruiting data. Figures provided are a single service estimate and are not official statistics.</p><p> </p><p>An applicant has been defined as someone who has applied and their data has been loaded onto the recruitment database.</p><p> </p><p>Reserves figures are for Group A Reserves. These are Reserves who are recruited through the National Recruiting Centre and are available for employment on specific tasks at home and overseas.</p><p> </p><p>Numbers have been rounded to the nearest 10. Numbers ending in five have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-12T13:54:54.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756804/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756804/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) men and (b) women have applied to join the Army since the commencement of the This is Belonging campaign.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7742"
