"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756807","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-11","<p>Information on the number of GCSEs held by new Army recruits and applicants to join the Army is not held. Only educational qualifications which are mandatory for the role applied for are captured.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","6918","2017-09-11T15:44:23.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756807/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756807/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756807/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-09-04","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people who have applied to join the Army since the commencement of the This is Belonging campaign have achieved five GCSEs with grades C and above.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7745"
