"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756835","Department of Health","false","2017-09-07","<p>The information requested is not held by the Department.</p><p> </p><p>The General Medical Council is the independent regulator of doctors in the United Kingdom and has provided the following information:</p><p>The number of registered doctors on the general practitioner (GP) Register with a licence to practise at close of business on 30 June 2017 was 60,833.</p><p> </p><p>The GP register covers the whole of the UK.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-07T10:21:12.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756835/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756835/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-04","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many GPs in Great Britain and Northern Ireland registered to practise there were on 1 July 2017.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","8228"
